-- Thailand Plans to Raise More Than $1.2 Billion Through 3G License Auction
-- Suttinee Yuvejwattana
-- 2010-07-03T09:33:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-03/thailand-plans-to-raise-more-than-1-2-billion-through-3g-license-auction.html

          
          
             Thailand aims to raise more than 38
billion baht ($1.2 billion) from a sale of three licenses for
high-speed mobile phone services, according to the National
Telecommunications Commission.  
 The starting price for a 15-year license for so-called
third-generation mobile phone technology will be 12.8 billion
baht. The auction will take place in September, Natee Sukonrat,
a member of the commission, told reporters today.  
